INFERENCE

From this experiment, it is inferred that the 8051 microcontroller efficiently performs arithmetic operations such as addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division on 8-bit and 16-bit data using its built-in instruction set. The Accumulator and B registers play a major role in these operations, while the carry and borrow flags are used to handle multi-byte calculations. By executing the programs on the 8051 Trainer Kit, the results were verified practically, improving understanding of data handling, instruction execution, and flag operations in microcontroller-based systems.



